message: Jennifer Thompson said, “This is the most traumatic things I’ve ever seen. Until we really address that there are people out there willing to pay for sexual encounters with minors and adults it's not going to go away. You can help victims and arrest traffickers all day long."

data.description: South Carolina Attorney General Alan Wilson recently released the state’s 2018 Annual Report on Human Trafficking.
data.title: SC makes big strides in fight against human trafficking
